files.file_summary: A module providing utility functions for cluster maintenance, monitoring, and administration in DolphinDB.
This module provides functionality for filtering and alerting on log messages in DolphinDB, including email notifications.
This script provides functions to parse and extract transaction-related information from DolphinDB log entries.
A log parsing module that processes DolphinDB log files, extracts relevant information, and stores results in either shared tables or DFS tables.
Provides configuration management and environment cleanup functions for the DolphinDB log analyzer.
A demo script for log analysis that loads required modules, initializes configuration, and processes logs either in batch or streaming mode.
Provides functionality for reading and parsing DolphinDB log files in both batch and streaming modes.
Provides utility functions for log analysis in DolphinDB, including querying log data by time range, level, and version comparison.
This module provides functionality to generate reports by processing errors and warnings from logs.

This file contains functions for parsing different types of transaction-related logs in DolphinDB, including transaction metrics, DB audit logs, and transaction lifecycle events (begin, closed, rolled back).
Provides functions for creating databases with specific configurations for different types of financial data.
Initializes the NSQ environment and sets up subscriptions for market data topics (orders, trade, snapshot) from specified exchanges (sh, sz) with optional DFS storage.
Facilitates automatic loading of trading data from DataYes into DolphinDB databases with configurable parameters.
Generates various transaction-related reports from log data including rolled back transactions, longest transactions, audit logs, metrics, and node-specific transaction details.
A module for subscribing to and managing NSQ real-time market data (orders, trades, snapshots) with options for stream tables and DFS storage.
Provides functionality to create and manage tables in DolphinDB for different market data types (snapshot, entrust, trade) with configurable market specifications.
Provides functions for loading and processing trading data files into DolphinDB databases.
Provides functions to load one day's worth of trading data for Shanghai and Shenzhen markets from CSV files into specified databases and tables.
This module provides functions for transforming and loading entrust data from Shanghai and Shenzhen markets into a standardized format in DolphinDB.
Defines table schemas for entrust CSV data in Shenzhen and Shanghai markets.
This module provides functions for transforming and loading Shanghai market trade and entrust data from CSV files into standardized database tables.
This module provides functions to transform and load trade data from Shanghai and Shenzhen markets into a standardized format in DolphinDB.
Provides functions for transforming and loading one day's worth of snapshot and order queue data for Shanghai and Shenzhen stock markets.
Defines schema structures for snapshot CSV data from Shenzhen and Shanghai markets, with different schemas based on trading dates.
Defines the schema for order queue CSV data with specific column names and types.
Defines the schema for trade and entrust CSV data for the Shanghai market.
Defines table schemas for entrust data in Shenzhen and Shanghai markets, with options to concatenate or separate trade date and time.
Defines table schemas for trade data in Shenzhen and Shanghai markets with options for time representation.
Defines table schemas for snapshot data of Shenzhen and Shanghai markets, with options to concatenate or separate trade date and time.
This file contains test cases for the alphalens function create_information_tear_sheet, verifying its functionality with different parameters.
This file tests the create_turnover_tear_sheet function in the alphalens module by validating its output structure and behavior with different parameters.
Defines table schemas for trade CSV data in Shenzhen and Shanghai markets based on trading day.
This file contains test cases for the alphalens function get_clean_factor_and_forward_returns, verifying its functionality with different parameters and scenarios.
This script tests the plot_create_full_tear_sheet function in the alphalens module with various configurations.
Tests the plot_quantile_statistics_table function from the alphalens module by analyzing factor data and verifying output structure and values.
This script tests the plot_create_returns_tear_sheet function in the alphalens module with various configurations.
This script implements and calculates the GTJA 191 alpha factors using DolphinDB modules gtja191Alpha and gtja191Prepare for a specific set of securities and time period.
This script implements the GTJA 191 alpha factors using DolphinDB modules gtja191Alpha and gtja191Prepare, calculates them for a set of securities, and saves the results.
This script creates a database and table for storing financial information data, then generates and populates it with sample data.
A DolphinDB implementation of the Alphalens library for performance analysis of alpha factors.
A DolphinDB module containing technical analysis indicators for financial time series data.
A DolphinDB module implementing technical analysis indicators from Tongdaxin () for financial market analysis.
A DolphinDB module implementing various technical analysis indicators similar to Python's TA-Lib.
This script implements real-time computation of WorldQuant 101 alpha factors using DolphinDB's streaming capabilities.
This script calculates and saves all 101 alpha factors into a database.
This script calculates and saves all 101 alpha factors into a database using DolphinDB.
This script tests the performance of WorldQuant 101 alpha implementations in DolphinDB by measuring execution times for each alpha.
This script verifies the correctness of WorldQuant 101 alpha implementations in DolphinDB by testing specific alpha functions on stock data.
This script verifies the correctness of WorldQuant 101 alpha implementation in DolphinDB by testing specific alpha factors on stock data.
Implements 101 alpha formulas from '101 Formulaic Alphas' in DolphinDB, categorized into factors with and without industry neutralization.
This module implements 191 alpha formulas from GuotaiJunan Securities in DolphinDB, categorized by their features and designed for day-level data analysis.
This script provides helper functions to prepare panel data and calculate 191 alpha factors for the gtja191Alpha module.
This script provides functions to prepare panel data and calculate 101 alpha factors for the wq101alpha module.
This script provides functions to prepare panel data and calculate 101 alpha factors for the wq101alpha module.
